# Keep the Docker build context small and stable so a Dockerfile-only edit
# doesn't bust the (expensive) DuckDB/cargo build layer. The server build
# (`cargo build -p escurel-server --features gemini`) only needs the cargo
# workspace: Cargo.{toml,lock}, rust-toolchain.toml, crates/, examples/.

# VCS + local build output (the cargo build runs inside the image).
.git
.gitignore
target
**/target

# The Dockerfile/.dockerignore themselves — excluding them means editing the
# Dockerfile leaves `COPY . .` unchanged, so the build cache survives.
Dockerfile
.dockerignore

# CI, docs, and the Flutter explore UI: not part of the cargo workspace.
.github
docs
apps

# Editor / OS cruft.
.DS_Store
*.swp
